          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-1" n="1">An Inundation (says the Fable)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-2" n="2">O'erflow'd a Farmers Barn and Stable</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-3" n="3">Whole Stacks of Hay &amp; Ricks of Corn</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-4" n="4">Were down the sudden Current born</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-5" n="5">While Things of heterogeneous Kind</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-6" n="6">Together Sail'd with Tide &amp; Wind</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-7" n="7">The honest wheat forgot his Pride</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-8" n="8">And Sail'd with Litter, Side by Side</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-9" n="9">Uniting All, to Shew their Amity</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-10" n="10">As in a general Calamity──</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-11" n="11">A Ball of new drop't Horses dung</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-12" n="12">Mingling with Apples on the Throng,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-13" n="13">Said to a Pippen large and Prim</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-14" n="14">See Brother, how we Apples swim</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-15" n="15">Thus Lamb renow'd for cutting Corns</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-16" n="16">A proffer'd Fee from Ratcliff scorns</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-17" n="17">Not for the world── we Doctors Brother</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-18" n="18">Must take no Fees from One another──</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-19" n="19">Thus to a Dean, some Curate sloven</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-20" n="20">Subscribes── D<hi rend="superscript">ṛ</hi> Sir your Brother loving─</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-21" n="21">Thus all the Footmen, Shooe Boys, Porters</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-22" n="22">About S<hi rend="superscript">ṭ</hi> James's cry── We Courtiers────</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-23" n="23">Thus Horace in the House will prate</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-24" n="24">Sir, We the ministers of State────</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-25" n="25">Thus at the Bar, that Booby B──</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-26" n="26">(Tho half a Crown o'erpays his Sweat's worth)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-27" n="27">Who knows in Law not Text nor Margent,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-28" n="28">Calls Singleton his Brother Serjeant.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-29" n="29">And thus Fanatick Saints tho neither in</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-30" n="30">Doctine or Dicipline, our Brethern</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-31" n="31">Are Brother Protestants &amp; Christians</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-32" n="32">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-33" n="33">But in no other Sense, than Nature</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-34" n="34">Has made a Rat our fellow Creature</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-35" n="35">Lice from your Body suck their Food</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-36" n="36">But is a Louse your Flesh and Blood?</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-37" n="37">Tho born of human Filth &amp; Sweet, It.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-38" n="38">\<hi rend="italics">add</hi>·Cannot be said, man did beget It────</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-39" n="39">The Maggots in your nose and Chin</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-40" n="40">As well may claim you for their Kin.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-41" n="41">But Criticks may object── why not</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-42" n="42">Since Lice are Brethren to a Scot</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-43" n="43">Which made our Swarm of Sects determine</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-44" n="44">Employments for their Brother Vermin</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-45" n="45">But be they English Irish, scottish</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-46" n="46">What Protestant can be so sottish</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-47" n="47">(While o'er the Church these Clouds are gath\'·<hi rend="italics">over</hi>·e\ring)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-48" n="48">To call a Swarm of Lice his Brethren</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-49" n="49">As Moses by divine Advice</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-50" n="50">in Egypt Turn'd the Dust to lice</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-51" n="51">And as our Sects by all Descriptions</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-52" n="52">Have Hearts more harden'd than Egyptians</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-53" n="53">As from the trodden Dust They Spring</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-54" n="54">And turn'd to Lice infest the King</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-55" n="55">For pity sake it were but just,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-56" n="56">A Rod should turn them back to Dust</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-57" n="57">Let men in high or holy Stations</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-58" n="58">Be proud of owning such Relations</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-59" n="59">Let Courtiers hug them in their Bosom</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-60" n="60">As if they were afraid to lose them</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-61" n="61">Whilst I with humble <hi rend="large-writing">Job</hi> had rather</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-62" n="62">Say to Corruption── Thou'rt my <hi rend="large-writing">Father</hi></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-63" n="63">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-811-410P-line-64" n="64">om.</l>
          </lg>
